go 1.25.0

use ./packages/devhex

// Canonical Go SDK workspace. Only packages/devhex (module
// github.com/KooshaPari/devenv-abstraction) is a member — it builds and tests
// clean and is the single source of the devenv/devhex modules.
//
// Removed 2026-06-02 (ADR-011 Go convergence): the two duplicate copies under
// packages/platformkit/go/ were dropped. They were carried "for reversibility"
// by the absorption subtree but were never built and were broken:
//   - platformkit/go/devhex: byte-divergent dup of packages/devhex with the SAME
//     module path (github.com/KooshaPari/devenv-abstraction) — a hard conflict.
//   - platformkit/go/devenv: older lowercase-path copy
//     (github.com/kooshapari/devenv-abstraction) that did not compile —
//     nonexistent mousetrap v1.1.2 pin, an import of a nonexistent
//     .../internal/domain remote, a package-name collision in internal/core,
//     and missing prometheus deps.
//
// PhenoMCP Go module decision unchanged: PhenoMCP retains its own module and is
// consumed as a dependency, not vendored. packages/mcpkit/go/go.work references
// not-yet-present pheno-mcp-* modules and stays deferred.
